This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on extractive document summarization. Additionally, the use of neural network architecture and training algorithms is a common theme in cs.CL. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as document summarization is a subfield of IR. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper discusses the effectiveness of representation learning and the use of neural network models. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possibility as the paper deals with the development of a novel model for document summarization, which is a task that falls under the umbrella of AI. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper focuses on the use of neural network models for document summarization.
